What is a server?
 - a computer program or software that provides services to a client
What is the role of the domain name?
 - To help in accessing servers since humans cannot remember ip addresses
What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com?
 - A record
What is the role of the web server?
 - To receive http requests from the client/user and submit reponses e.g in form of web pages
What is the role of the application server?
 - Provides logic and functionality which produce dynamic web pages depending on client's request
What is the role of the database?
 - To have a place to store and retrieve data needed when necessary
What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website?
 - A http response

SPOF In the system.
 - The system lack redundancy where only one server, database and web server are used such that if one of them fails the whole system comes to a halt

Downtime when maintenance needed (like deploying new code web server needs to be restarted)
 - Since we only have one server, when its being restarted after deploying new code the users will suffer downtime since there is no backup server
Cannot scale if too much incoming traffic
 - The system is not scalable without having to halt everything and using a new infrastructure.

